===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|bishop|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|biscop||bishop|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|VL.}} *{{term||biscopus|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|episcopus||overseer, supervisor|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|ἐπίσκοπος||overseer|tr=episkopos|sc=polytonic}}, from {{term|ἐπί||over|tr=epi|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|σκοπέω||I examine|tr=skopeō|sc=polytonic}}. Cognate with {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|biskop||bishop|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|bisschop||bishop|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Bischof||bishop|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|biskop||bishop|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|no|-}} {{term|biskop||bishop|lang=no}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|biskup||bishop|lang=is}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|||tr=aipiskaupus|bishop|lang=got}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈbɪʃəp/}}
* {{audio|En-us-bishop.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A high ranking official in the Catholic church who governs a [[diocese]], or a similar official in other denominations and religions. (Occasionally abbreviated as {{term|Bp.|lang=en}} when used as a [[title]].)
# {{chess}} A [[piece]] that may be moved only diagonally.
#: ''The '''bishop''' is confined to squares of a single color.''
# {{slang}} [[penis]] (see [[bash the bishop]]).
# {{slang}} [[sex toy]].

